  "prompt": "Which authors inspire Dushka Zapata?",
  "response": "Dushka Zapata has mentioned several authors who have inspired her work. Some of these include:\n\n1. **Haruki Murakami** - Known for his surrealistic storytelling, Murakami's ability to blend the ordinary with the extraordinary has influenced Zapata's own narrative style.\n\n2. **Gabriel Garc\u00eda M\u00e1rquez** - The magical realism and rich storytelling of M\u00e1rquez have left a significant impact on Zapata, particularly in how she weaves cultural elements into her writing.\n\n3. **Franz Kafka** - Kafka's existential themes and his exploration of alienation and absurdity resonate with Zapata, influencing her approach to character development and thematic depth.\n\n4. **Ana\u00efs Nin** - Nin's introspective and often diaristic style has inspired Zapata to explore the inner lives of her characters with greater depth and sensitivity.\n\n5. **Virginia Woolf** - Woolf's stream-of-consciousness technique and focus on the psychological aspects of her characters have influenced Zapata's own methods of character portrayal and narrative structure.\n\nThese authors have shaped Zapata's writing through their unique styles, thematic concerns, and innovative approaches to storytelling.",
